## Installation :
https://github.com/yuk7/ArchWSL

## Configuration
$ pacman-key --init #Install and populate pacman Key 
$ pacman-key --populate #Needed to use pacman

$ passwd #Change Root password

$ useradd -m rcandau #Create our user
$ passwd rcandau #Change his password
$ usermod -aG wheel rcandau #Put it in the wheel group so he can use sudo

$ export EDITOR=/usr/bin/vim #Make vim our default editor to edit the sudo configuration file
$ visudo #Uncomment line that allows wheel group members to use sudo on any command

-- This two following commands has to be launch in the windows cmd --
$ cd Documents\Arch\ #Change directory to our directory that contains Arch Linux WSL
$ Arch.exe config --default-user rcandau #Make Arch log into our regular user at launch instead of root

$ sudo pacman -Syu #Update our system
$ sudo pacman -S base-devel linux-headers man bash-completion openssh inetutils dnsutils traceroute rsync zip unzip cronie diffutils tmux mlocate htop neofetch #Install my needed packages. DO NOT INSTALL "fakeroot" (https://github.com/yuk7/ArchWSL/issues/3)

-- Install my config files --
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Antiz96/Linux-Customisation/master/Dotfiles/bashrc%20(Arch%20Based%20Distro%20-%20WSL) #.bashrc
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Antiz96/Linux-Customisation/master/Dotfiles/tmux.conf #.tmux.conf

 




